        "title": "fix(cli): harden Windows node pairing and approvals",
        "body": "## Summary\n- preserve existing untagged device tokens for same-key metadata refresh approvals when the token was already valid before the approval\n- keep rotating for scope expansion, public-key repair, stale baseline tokens, revoked/issuer-tagged tokens, incompatible role/scopes, and malformed persisted token entries\n- add pairing token regression coverage for Windows node reconnect churn and unsafe reuse boundaries\n- make devices/nodes/gateway CLI RPC helpers use the direct local gateway-client admin path for explicit loopback token/password auth, avoiding stale paired CLI identity/scope traps\n- make `approvals get --node` tolerate host-native Windows exec policy payloads instead of crashing on the local approvals-file shape\n\n## Validation\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/infra/device-pairing.test.ts`: 60 passed\n- `pnpm test:serial src/cli/devices-cli.test.ts src/cli/nodes-cli/register.invoke.approval-transport-timeout.test.ts src/cli/gateway-rpc.runtime.test.ts src/cli/gateway-cli.coverage.test.ts src/cli/exec-approvals-cli.test.ts`: 102 passed\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode branch --base origin/main`: clean, no accepted/actionable findings\n- `OPENCLAW_TESTBOX=1 pnpm check:changed`: passed core/coreTests lanes in Blacksmith Testbox `tbx_01ksvjj88w72t42mxys62kmjqd` / run `26674605097`\n- Azure pond: signed Windows prerelease launches; operator pairing approved; node role upgrade approved; Windows node registered and reported 1/1 online\n- Azure pond after `432c9fe`: gateway rebuilt/restarted, Windows node stayed paired/connected, `approvals get --node --json` returned host-native policy (`defaultAction=deny`, 21 rules), `system.run` allowed `echo openclaw-exec-ok`, and denied `Start-Process notepad` with `Command denied by exec policy: Block process launch`\n\n## Notes\nStill draft so Vincent can review before this becomes merge-ready.\n",
